bug.short_desc: [abrt] cinnamon: g_desktop_app_info_get_is_hidden(): cinnamon killed by SIGSEGV
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext: Description of problem: cinnamon appeared to crash during operation. The most recent time, I was upating Calibre using the commands from calibre's website, but it has happened seemingly at random. However, since the commoon factor appears to be that system folders are accessed, I wonder if the issue is in the security policies? ( specifically, since I have had issues with my account no longer working in the past, and the common factor is system folders needing to be accessed...) Version-Release number of selected component: cinnamon-3.0.6-1.fc24 Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.7.1 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: cinnamon --replace crash_function: g_desktop_app_info_get_is_hidden executable: /usr/bin/cinnamon global_pid: 1579 kernel: 4.6.3-300.fc24.x86_64 pkg_fingerprint: 73BD E983 81B4 6521 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project reproducible: Not sure how to reproduce the problem runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1001 Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (9 frames) #0 g_desktop_app_info_get_is_hidden at gdesktopappinfo.c:2019 #1 desktop_entry_get_hidden at desktop-entries.c:616 #2 process_layout at gmenu-tree.c:3690 #4 gmenu_tree_build_from_layout at gmenu-tree.c:4767 #5 gmenu_tree_load_sync at gmenu-tree.c:745 #6 on_apps_tree_changed_cb at cinnamon-app-system.c:349 #7 _g_closure_invoke_va at gclosure.c:867 #10 menu_layout_invoke_monitors at menu-layout.c:154 #15 meta_run at core/main.c:542 Potential duplicate: bug 1036446
